# Tool Coverage Checklist

When adding, removing, or modifying an MCP tool in pm-copilot, always update **all three locations** before considering the work done:

## 1. Tool registration (`src/index.ts`)
- Add the tool to the `TOOLS` array with `name`, `description`, and `inputSchema`.
- Add a `case` in the `switch` block to dispatch to the implementation function.
- Update the import at the top of the file.

## 2. Tests (`tests/tools.test.ts`)
- Import the new function.
- Add at least one test: a callable/dry-run check for write operations, or a live integration test for read operations.
- If the tool output format changed, update any assertions that match on output strings.

## 3. README (`README.md`)
- Add the tool to the appropriate table under **Available Tools**.
- Update the tool count in the heading (e.g. "Available Tools (18)").
- If a new integration category was added, add a new table section.

## Quick audit
Before finishing, mentally cross-check: every `name:` in the `TOOLS` array in `index.ts` must appear in both `tools.test.ts` and `README.md`.
